odation, Interculturalism is the first clear and comprehensive statement in English of an approach being discussed around the world.A translation of Bouchard’s award-winning French-language work, L’Interculturalisme: Un point de vue québécois, this book features a new foreword by philosopher Charles Taylor and an afterword by the author written specifically for the English-language edition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aCultural pluralismzQuébec (Province). 0aCultural pluralism. 0aLaicism. 0aMulticulturalism. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aScott, Howard.1 aTaylor, Charles.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311060681240uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266910940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442669109423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442669109.jpg  a978-3-11-060681-2  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles